  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "In https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/cloudprovider/servicecontroller/servicecontroller.go, I found a logic error (when I had a broken cloud implementation):\n\nIf createLoadBalancerIfNeeded returns err, then cachedService will have service = nil.  This causes updateLoadBalancerHosts to panic.\n\nIt would be easy to skip cacheService if service=nil, but I wasn't sure whether this should then be included in servicesToRetry or not. \n\nAnother problem (by inspection) is that I think there's a race condition where updateLoadBalancerHosts can run immediately after getOrCreate, before the service field has been set. \n",
